lover /ˈlʌvə/

(lovers) 

1. N-COUNT Someone's lover is someone who they are having a sexual relationship with but are not married to. 情人 

例： Every Thursday she would meet her lover Leon. 每个星期四她都去约会她的情人利昂。 

2. N-COUNT If you are a lover of something such as animals or the arts, you enjoy them very much and take great pleasure in them. 爱好者 

例： She is a great lover of horses and horse racing. 她非常喜欢马，并热衷于赛马。

